<HEADLINE>
<P>
'BAD SCENE IN SOUTH TEXAS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Bad scene in South Texas" has the INS and the refugees from Nicaragua between 
a "rock and a hard place." Members of Congress, above all, must be held 
responsible for their procrastination and ineptitude in developing a logical 
immigration policy. Their lack of prescience in the "on again, off again" 
penurious funding of the Contras would have made a difference in the lives of 
their citizens had they funded the Contras properly. 
</P>
<P>
Not unlike a plague, the Nicaraguans, now considered refugees, are joined by 
the people of El Salvador and Guatemala inundating our ports of entry on our 
southern border. 
</P>
<P>
Until the political, socioeconomic conditions improve they shall continue to 
deluge our borders. 
</P>
<P>
"We inherit the wind!" 
</P>
<P>
SAMUEL S. SHERWIN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
