</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELLIOTT TEAFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All four Orange County girls' basketball teams that played in Southern Section 
championship games last week have advanced to the Southern California regional 
playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
First-round games are Tuesday at 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon, Katella and Valencia high schools advanced to the Division II playoffs. 
And Brea-Olinda, which breezed to the Southern Section 3-A title, advanced to 
the Division III playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
Brea (27-2), the top-seeded team, will play host to Our Lady of Peace (19-6) of 
the San Diego Section. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon (22-5) will play at top-seeded Vista (26-3) in the Division II brackets. 
Canyon lost to Valencia, 56-45, in the Southern Section 4-AA final Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Katella (26-3), which won the school's first Southern Section basketball title 
with a 54-48 overtime victory over Muir in the 4-A final Thursday, plays host 
to San Marcos of San Diego (26-3). 
</P>
<P>
Valencia (20-9) plays host to Mt. Whitney of Visalia (23-2). ELLIOTT TEAFORD 
</P>
