BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Purchasing Managers See Slowdown: Economic growth slowed in February, easing 
inflation pressures that have pushed short-term interest rates to the highest 
level in four years, the National Assn. of Purchasing Management said. In its 
monthly report based on a survey of purchasing executives at 250 companies, the 
trade group said the U.S. economy expanded but at an even slower rate than the 
sluggish growth seen in January. The group's leading purchasing management 
index was 53% in February, nearly unchanged from 53.2% in January. The previous 
low for the index was 52.6% in February, 1987. The index is a composite of new 
orders, production, deliveries, inventories and employment. 
</P>
