<P>
ARAB PRISONER DIES, 2 OTHERS KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Palestinian died in Israeli detention today and troops shot two Arab 
protesters to death in one of the most violent days in the occupied territories 
in several weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Security sources said Mahmoud Yousef Masri, 34, of Rafah was found dead in the 
Shin Bet secret police's interrogation room at Gaza Central Prison. Palestinian 
sources charged that he was beaten to death. Israel Radio quoted security 
officials as saying he was treated for stomach ulcers shortly before dying. One 
teen-ager died in a clash between stone-throwers and soldiers in Gaza's Jabalya 
refugee camp and a 24-year-old man was killed during a search-and-arrest 
operation in Salem in the West Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
