<P>
TRAFFIC JAM IN VALLEY FAILS TO OCCUR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Traffic moved slowly but major problems failed to materialize today on the 
Ventura Freeway when five ramps were closed as part of a lengthy widening 
project, the California Highway Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
"We expected a major traffic tie-up but it went really smooth this morning," 
CHP Sgt. Steve Santoro said. "It was stop-and-go traffic, but it moved quicker 
than expected. I think a lot of people took heed and scheduled more time for 
their commute. If they followed directions, they had an easy commute." 
</P>
<P>
Ramps that were closed include the westbound on-ramp at Topanga Canyon 
Boulevard, the westbound off-ramp at Parkway Calabasas, the westbound and 
eastbound off-ramps at Valley Circle and the eastbound off-ramp at Fallbrook 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Caltrans opened two freeway bypass routes in Woodland Hills to help ease the 
flow of traffic to and from areas such as the Warner Center and Calabasas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
