<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH STUDENT KILLED AS MOTORCYCLE COLLIDES WITH CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 16-year-old Huntington Beach High School student died Sunday night when the 
motorcycle on which she was a passenger hit a car, police said. Leslie Groosman 
died instantly in the 10:39 p.m. accident on Pacific Coast Highway, north of 
Warner Avenue, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Neither Groosman nor the driver of the motorcycle, Scott Melnyzok, 18, was 
wearing a helmet, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Melnyzok was treated for a concussion and cuts at Fountain Valley Community 
Hospital, then taken to Orange County Jail, where he was booked on suspicion of 
manslaughter and felony drunk driving. The driver of the car, Randy Seymour, 
32, of Garden Grove, was uninjured. 
</P>
<P>
Seymour said he did not see other vehicles around him before the accident 
occurred. "It's like they came out of nowhere," he said. "When I pulled over, I 
still didn't know what hit me." 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach High Principal Gary Ernst announced Groosman's death to 
students at 11:30 a.m. today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
