<P>
RAMIREZ GETS 3RD DEFENSE LAWYER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A third defense lawyer was appointed today to assist accused Night Stalker 
Richard Ramirez's two other attorneys, one of whom has complained of "nervous 
exhaustion" because of work overload. 
</P>
<P>
Superior Court Judge Michael Tynan announced the appointment of Los Angeles 
attorney Ray Clark as the trial was about to resume after a two-week recess. 
Clark will assist Ramirez's other attorneys, Daniel Hernandez and Arturo 
Hernandez, who have been representing the accused serial killer since late 
1985. Daniel Hernandez complained last week of suffering from "nervous 
exhaustion" because of a work overload stemming from the trial. 
</P>
