<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ARIZONA'S COOK TOP PAC-10 CAGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WALNUT CREEK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Arizona forward Anthony Cook was named the Pac-10 Conference men's basketball 
player of the week today. The 6-foot-9 senior from Los Angeles paced the 
Wildcats to their second Pac-10 championship with a 17-1 conference play record 
after road wins at Washington State (74-48) and at UCLA (89-86). Cook scored 45 
points and 25 rebounds in those two games last week, shooting 60% from the 
floor. He had 28 points and nine rebounds against the Cougars; with a 17 and 12 
tally against the Bruins. Cook also managed four steals and four blocked shots 
against UCLA and Washington State. 
</P>
</TEXT>
